      <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--gd-text-2);margin-bottom:3px;">z = 1.000</div>
      <div style="font-family:var(--gd-font-mono);font-size:14px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gd-brand);">0.841</div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:var(--gd-bg-3);border:1px solid var(--gd-line-soft);border-radius:8px;padding:8px;text-align:center;">
      <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--gd-text-2);margin-bottom:3px;">z = 1.500</div>
      <div style="font-family:var(--gd-font-mono);font-size:14px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gd-brand);">0.933</div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:var(--gd-bg-3);border:1px solid var(--gd-line-soft);border-radius:8px;padding:8px;text-align:center;">
      <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--gd-text-2);margin-bottom:3px;">z = 1.645</div>
      <div style="font-family:var(--gd-font-mono);font-size:14px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gd-brand);">0.950</div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:var(--gd-bg-3);border:1px solid var(--gd-line-soft);border-radius:8px;padding:8px;text-align:center;">
      <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--gd-text-2);margin-bottom:3px;">z = 1.960</div>
      <div style="font-family:var(--gd-font-mono);font-size:14px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gd-brand);">0.975</div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:var(--gd-bg-3);border:1px solid var(--gd-line-soft);border-radius:8px;padding:8px;text-align:center;">
      <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--gd-text-2);margin-bottom:3px;">z = 2.000</div>
      <div style="font-family:var(--gd-font-mono);font-size:14px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gd-brand);">0.977</div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:var(--gd-bg-3);border:1px solid var(--gd-line-soft);border-radius:8px;padding:8px;text-align:center;">
      <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--gd-text-2);margin-bottom:3px;">z = 2.576</div>
      <div style="font-family:var(--gd-font-mono);font-size:14px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gd-brand);">0.995</div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:var(--gd-bg-3);border:1px solid var(--gd-line-soft);border-radius:8px;padding:8px;text-align:center;">
      <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--gd-text-2);margin-bottom:3px;">z = 3.000</div>
      <div style="font-family:var(--gd-font-mono);font-size:14px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gd-brand);">0.999</div>
    </div>
    <div style="background:var(--gd-bg-3);border:1px solid var(--gd-peri-line);border-radius:8px;padding:8px;text-align:center;">
      <div style="font-size:12px;color:var(--gd-text-2);margin-bottom:3px;">symmetry</div>
      <div style="font-family:var(--gd-font-mono);font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--gd-brand);">Φ(−z)=1−Φ(z)</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--gd-text-2);margin:8px 0 0;">1.645 and 1.96 reappear in Module 1.8 for 90% and 95% confidence intervals.</p>
</div>

<div class="gd-insights">
  <div class="gd-insight gd-insight--warn">
    <span class="gd-insight__title">$N(\mu, \sigma^2)$ — second parameter is variance, not SD</span>
    $X \sim N(5, 4)$ means $\mu=5$, $\sigma^2=4$, so $\sigma=\sqrt&#123;4&#125;=2$. Standardize with $\sigma$, not $\sigma^2$: $z=(x-5)/2$. Writing $z=(x-5)/4$ is the classic trap. (2025 Q20)
  </div>
  <div class="gd-insight gd-insight--insight">
    <span class="gd-insight__title">Three steps for every Normal question</span>
    (1) Identify $\mu$ and $\sigma^2$. &nbsp; (2) Compute $\sigma = \sqrt&#123;\sigma^2&#125;$. &nbsp; (3) Standardize: $z = (x-\mu)/\sigma$, then look up $\Phi(z)$. Use symmetry $\Phi(-z)=1-\Phi(z)$ to avoid negative-z lookups.
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══ VIZ 1: Z-TABLE / AREA UNDER CURVE ═══ -->
<h2 id="viz1">Interactive 1 — Area Under the Bell Curve</h2>
<p style="font-size:15px;color:var(--gd-text-1);margin-bottom:16px;line-height:1.6;">
  Drag sliders to set $[a, b]$. Shaded area = $\Phi(b) - \Phi(a)$. Use presets to see the 68/95/99.7 rule and confidence-interval cut-points.
</p>

<div class="gd-formula-panel gd-formula-panel--split">
  <div>
    <div class="gd-formula-label">Standard Normal Z ~ N(0,1)</div>
    <div class="gd-formula">$$P(a \le Z \le b) = \Phi(b) - \Phi(a)$$</div>
  </div>
  <div>
    <div class="gd-formula-label">Current area</div>
    <div class="prob-display" id="area-display">P = —</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="gd-chart" style="position:relative;">
  <div class="gd-chart__title">Shaded area = P(a ≤ Z ≤ b)</div>
  <div id="normal-chart"></div>
</div>

<div class="gd-controls">
